      <item>
        <title>Integrate Bootstrap &amp; react-picker</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[luisherranz]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>You can use both bootstrap or react-picker without any problem with Frontity.</p>
<p>The only problem right now is how to import the CSS using Emotion.</p>
<p>We are going to work on a solution as stated here:</p>
<aside class="quote" data-post="1" data-topic="305">
  <div class="title">
    <div class="quote-controls"></div>
    <img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/w/ea666f/40.png" class="avatar">
    <a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/use-zurb-foundation-with-frontity/305">Use zurb foundation with frontity</a> <a class="badge-wrapper  box" href="https://community.frontity.org/c/dev-talk-questions"><span class="badge-category-bg" style="background-color: #3AB54A;"></span><span style="color: #FFFFFF" data-drop-close="true" class="badge-category clear-badge" title="Share with the community how are you going to use Frontity!
Confused? Getting a weird error? Just want to share your progress? Also your place.">🤗 Dev Talk &amp; Questions</span></a>
  </div>
  <blockquote>
    Hi 
How can I use foundation framework with frontity?
  </blockquote>
</aside>

<p>Something like this:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-javascript">import { Global, css } from 'frontity';
import Picker from 'react-picker';
import pickerStyles from "react-picker/css/picker.css";

const MyTheme = () =&gt; (
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;Global styles={css(pickerStyles)} /&gt;
    &lt;Picker /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
);
</code></pre>
<p>We’ll let you know once it’s ready <img src="https://community.frontity.org/images/emoji/apple/slight_smile.png?v=9" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"></p>
